    dc:title "A new divergent lineage of Daphnia (Cladocera: Anomopoda) and its morphological and genetical differentiation from Daphnia curvirostris Eylmann, 1887" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687395>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687399>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687401>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687385>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687381> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687395>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Daphnia tanakai sp. nov. from Lake Midori-ga-ike, collected on August 30, 2004 by S. Tanaka (A–F, K–O) and Lake Kagami-ike, collected on September 01, 2004 by S. Tanaka (G–J, P–R); both lakes are in Hida Mountain Range, Honshu Island, Japan. A, parthenogenetic female, lateral view. B, head of parthenogenetic female. C, D, armature of postero-ventral and posterior region of valve. E, postabdomen. F–I, postabdominal claws of adults. J, postabdominal claw of juvenile. K, L, antenna I in lateral and distal view. M, N, distal portion of basal segment in posterior and anterior view. O, swimming seta. P, Q, ephippial female and postero-dorsal portion of its carapace. R, ephippium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4687395/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687399>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Daphnia tanakai sp. nov., thoracic limbs of parthenogenetic female from Lake Midori-ga-ike, Japan. A, B, limb I. C, D, anterior seta on its endite 3 and 2. E, limb II. F, G, stiff seta on its inner-distal end. H, gnathobase II. I, J, limb III and its inner-distal portion. K, L, limb IV and its inner-distal portion. M, N, limb V and distal portion of its exopodite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4687399/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687401>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Daphnia tanakai sp. nov., male from Lake Midori-ga-ike, Japan. A, lateral view. B, caudal spine. C, head. D, E, armature of antero-ventral and posterior portion of valve. F, G, postabdomen and postabdominal claw. H, male antenna I. I, tip of male seta (‘flagellum’) on antenna I. J, K, limb I and its distal portion. L–O, distal-most endite of limb II." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4687401/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687385>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Mapping the characters of chromosome number and postabdominal claw morphology onto the Daphnia ND2 consensus tree (Fig. 1). A, the left cladogram shows the evolution of chromosome number. Black line denotes 2n = 22, white line denotes 2n = 20 and dot line denotes 2n = 24. B, the right cladogram shows the evolution of postabdominal claw morphology. Black line denotes variable phenotype between the longispina-claw and pulex-claw types, white line denotes the longispina- claw type, dot line denotes the pulex-claw type and grey line denotes equivocal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4687385/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687381>
    dc:description "Figure 1. ME bootstrap consensus tree of Daphnia ND2 sequences. The numbers on each branch show support values of the branch. Upper numbers indicate ME, and ML bootstrap support values for nucleotide sequences. Middle numbers indicate MP bootstrap support values and Bayesian clade credibility values for nucleotide sequences. Lower numbers indicate MP bootstrap support values and Bayesian clade credibility values for amino acid sequences. Asterisks indicate no support values." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4687381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

